==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prepotency
<hw>Pre*po"ten*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praepotentia</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pr⟦eacute⟧potence</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or condition of being prepotent;
predominance.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p> <sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The capacity, on the part of one
of the parents, as compared with the other, to transmit more than his or
her own share of characteristics to their offspring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prepotent</ent>⟦br⟧
